<i>February–March</i>:<br />25,000 men (fewer than 12,000 are armed troops; the rest are unarmed logistical troops)<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEOlson1989107_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEOlson1989107-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br /><i>April</i>:<br />52,000 men (25,000 are armed troops)<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEOlson1989107_1-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEOlson1989107-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td><td style="width:50%;padding-left:0.25em">
15,000 men<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEOlson1989107_1-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEOlson1989107-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th colspan="2" style="background-color:#C3D6EF;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle;font-size:110%;">Casualties and losses</th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center">
