<li><a href="/wiki/Serhildan" title="Serhildan">Serhildan</a></li></ul>
</div></td></tr><tr><td class="navbox-abovebelow" colspan="2" style="background-color:#DCDCDC;"><div>1. <a href="/wiki/Alevism" title="Alevism">Alevi</a>+<a href="/wiki/Kurds_in_Turkey" title="Kurds in Turkey">Kurdish</a> rebellion,<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> 2. <a href="/wiki/Zazas" title="Zazas">Zaza</a> rebellion<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></div></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<p>The <b>Sheikh Said Rebellion</b> (<a href="/wiki/Kurdish_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Kurdish language">Kurdish</a>: <span lang="ku" dir="rtl">Serhildana Şêx Seîd</span>,<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Turkish_language" title="Turkish language">Turkish</a>: <i lang="tr">Şeyh Said İsyanı</i>) or <b>Genç Incident</b> (<a href="/wiki/Turkish_language" title="Turkish language">Turkish</a>: <i lang="tr">Genç Hâdisesi</i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Kurds" title="Kurds">Kurdish</a> <a href="/wiki/Kurdish_nationalism" title="Kurdish nationalism">nationalist</a> rebellion in <a href="/wiki/Turkish_Kurdistan" title="Turkish Kurdistan">Turkish Kurdistan</a> in 1925 led by <a href="/wiki/Sheikh_Said" title="Sheikh Said">Sheikh Said</a> and with support of the <a href="/wiki/Azad%C3%AE" title="Azadî">Civata Xweseriya Kurd (Society for Kurdish Independence)</a><sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEOlson198942_6-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEOlson198942-6">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> against the newly-founded <a href="/wiki/Turkey" title="Turkey">Turkish Republic</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> The rebellion was mostly led by <a href="/wiki/Zazas" title="Zazas">Zaza speakers</a>, but also gained support among some of the neighboring <a href="/wiki/Kurmanji" title="Kurmanji">Kurmanji</a> speaking <a href="/wiki/Kurds" title="Kurds">Kurds</a> in the region.<sup id="cite_ref-Kaya2011_8-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Kaya2011-8">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> 
</p><p>The religious and nationalist background of the Sheikh Said Rebellion has been debated by the scholars.<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> The rebellion was described as "the first large-scale <a href="/wiki/Kurdish_nationalism" title="Kurdish nationalism">nationalist rebellion by the Kurds</a>." by Robert W. Olson.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEOlson1989153_10-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEOlson1989153-10">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
